            <thetext>The constructor of qx.ui.core.MBlocker creates a ui.core.Blocker instance which attaches an &quot;appear&quot; listener to the widget. Because of this listener, the offsetWidth property of the widget&#39;s DOM element is queried every time the Element queue is flushed. This can be a fairly costly operation which we should avoid if possible, especially considering that qx.ui.root.Abstract includes MBlocker.</thetext>
